name: Anticipation
effect: The first time each Round you are targeted by an attack that would deal Super-Effective damage, that attack gains +1 Bane to its Accuracy Roll.

name: Battle Armor
effect: You take normal damage from Critical Hits.

name: Hustle
effect: +6/8/10 Damage and +1 Bane to Accuracy for all Physical Melee Strikes.

name: Impudent
effect: Moves with the Social Keyword have +1 Bane on Accuracy Rolls against you.

name: Keen Eye
effect: You ignore any Banes to Accuracy caused by Moves, Abilities, or Talents.

name: Leek Wielder
effect: Your attacks gain a +2 bonus to Critical Hit Range.

name: Limber
effect: You are immune to paralysis.

name: Long Limbs
effect: You gain +1 Reach.

name: Natural Cure
effect: Once per Scene, when recalled into a Poke Ball, you may cure yourself of one Mental or Physical Status Condition.

name: Physical Armor
effect: +3/4/5 Armor vs Physical Damage.

name: Physical Attacker
effect: You deal +3/4/5 Damage with Physical Strikes.

name: Poison Skin
effect: Once a Scene, when a foe hits you with a Melee attack, you can cause them to gain Ongoing Damage 5/8/10 (Poison, Save Ends).

name: Quick Feet
effect: You may Sprint for 1 AP instead of 2 AP.

name: Run Away
effect: Whenever you would become Slowed or Stuck, roll a Save. On a success, remove the triggering condition.

name: Sap Sipper
effect: You are Immune to Grass-type attacks, and when hit by a Grass-type Attack, your next Physical Strike deals +1d6 Damage.

name: Shield Dust
effect: You are Immune to effects that activate on Critical or Super-Effective Hit.

name: Soundproof
effect: You are Immune to all effects and damage from Moves with the Sonic Keyword.

name: Special Armor
effect: You have +3/4/5 Armor vs Special Damage.

name: Special Attacker
effect: You deal +3/4/5 Damage with Special Strikes.

name: Spinning Dance
effect: Once a Round when you are missed by an attack, you may gain +2 to all Defenses for one full round, then Disengage 1.

name: Static
effect: Once a Scene, when a foe hits you with a Melee attack, you can cause them to become Paralyzed (save ends).

name: Two-Faced
effect: While you have uses left of Ice Face, you have +3/4/5 Armor vs Physical Damage. While you have no uses left of Ice Face, you have +3 Initiative and +2 Movement.
